Brazil Stock Movers: Brookfield, Brasil Foods, Cosan, Tecnisa

-- B y   A l e x a n d e r   C u a d r o s
-- 
2011-06-02T20:22:12Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-02/brazilian-stock-movers-brasil-foods-cosan-gerdau-marfrig.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Sao Paulo trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4:15 p.m. New York time.
Preferred shares are usually the most-traded class of stock.  The Bovespa Index gained 1.3 percent to 64,218.08.  Brookfield Incorporacoes SA (BISA3)  (BISA3 BS) jumped 4.9 percent
to 8.55 reais while  Tecnisa SA (TCSA3)  (TCSA3 BS) gained 4.3 percent to
13.08 reais. The companies were among Brazilian homebuilders
rated “buy” in new coverage at Banco BTG Pactual SA.  BRF  Brasil Foods  SA (BRFS3 BS) slipped 1.7 percent to 28.60
reais. Russia banned imports from 85 Brazilian beef plants as of
June 15, the country’s health authority said. The ban includes
operations of Brasil Foods.  Cosan SA Industria e Comercio (CSAN3)  (CSAN3 BS) jumped 4.8 percent
to 24.25 reais. Cosan said in a filing it will transfer about
5.24 billion reais ($3.3 billion) in net debt to its Raizen
sugar-cane processing venture with Royal Dutch Shell Plc. The
company also is “very inclined” to buy back shares, Chief
Financial Officer Marcelo Martins said today on a conference
call.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alexander Cuadros in  Sao Paulo  at 
 acuadros@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
